      <description>From 13 to 24 April 2026, 34 specialists in victim identification from Europol, INTERPOL and 31 countries worldwide gathered at Europol’s headquarters in The Hague to identify victims and perpetrators of child sexual exploitation cases. As a result of the taskforce, 12 children were tentatively identified.</description>
